extends layout

block content
    div(class="jumbotron")
        div(class="container")
            h1
                | Basics
    div(class="")
        div(class="well")
            h2 
                | Application
            p
                | To integrate the experiance we will need an application. You can create an application on 
                a(href="https://developers.facebook.com/apps/", target="_blank")
                    | https://developers.facebook.com/apps/
                | This will require to be a verified user. For help to becoming one look at 
                a(href="https://www.facebook.com/help/www/266902903322428", target="_blank")
                    | https://www.facebook.com/help/www/266902903322428
    div(class="")
        div(class="well")
            h2 
                | OAuth2.0
            p
                | Facebook's authentication flows are based on the OAuth 2.0 protocol. You can learn more about the protocol at 
                a(href="http://oauth.net/2/", target="_blank")
                    | http://oauth.net/2/
    div(class="")
        div(class="well")
            h2 
                | Permissions
            p
                | When a person logs into your app via Facebook Login you can access a subset of that person's data stored on Facebook. Permissions are how you ask someone if you can access that data. A person's privacy settings combined with what you ask for will determine what you can access.
    div(class="")
        div(class="well")
            h2 
                |  Access Tokens
            p
                | When someone connects with an app using Facebook Login, the app will be able to obtain an access token which provides temporary, secure access to Facebook APIs.
     div(class="")
        div(class="well")
            h2 
                | Tools
            p
                | A number of tools are available for us at 
                a(href="https://developers.facebook.com/tools/") 
                    | https://developers.facebook.com/tools/